Mary Warrin, affirms to y$^e$ Jury of Inquest. that: she hath
been afflicted by Giles Cory or his apparition and
that by beating of me with his staffe: & by biting me
pinching & choaking me greatly torturing me & cutting me
with a knife. & particularly at y$^e$ time of his examination
he did greavously torment me: also: at the time of his
examination. I saw: s$^d$ Cory or his apparition most dread-
fully afflict: Mary Walcot Ann Putnam: mercy lewis &
Sarah: Vibber Sept$^r$: 9: 1692

Eliz Woodwell upon y$^e$ oath she formerly has taken in
this Court: did affirm to y$^e$ Jury of Inquest: that: she saw
Giles Cory at meeting at Salem on a lecture day. since
he has bin at prison he or his apparition: came in &
sat: in y$^e$ middlemost seat: of y$^e$ mens seats: by y$^e$ post
this was lecture day before: Bridget Bishop was hanged
and I saw him come out: with y$^e$ rest of y$^e$ people: at y$^e$ time
Mary Walcot: affirmed: she saw s$^d$ Cory: as above: sitting y$^e$
same place at y$^e$ same time he or his appearance & she
saw him goe out: with y$^e$ rest of y$^e$ people: this she affirmes
to y$^e$ Jury of Inquest: Sept$^r$ 9: 1692

Eliz Hubbard: to y$^e$ Jury of Inquest: that Giles Cory hath several
times afflicted me with several sorts of torments: I veryly think
he is a wizard & afflicted me by witchcraft Sept$^r$ 9: 1692